                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <h2>How to Fill the Excel Sheet (By Institution Type)</h2>
                        <h2>School Use Case</h2>
                        <h3>Classes 1-8 (Primary and Middle School)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Class:</b> Enter the class number (e.g. 5, 6, 7..etc)</li>
                            <li><b>Semester:</b> Leave Empty</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> Enter all subjects taught to the class</li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Optionals / Minors:</b> Usually not applicable in most schools; leave empty unless
                                your school follows a different structure.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><b>Example Table:</b></p>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Class</th>
                                    <th>Semester</th>
                                    <th>Majors</th>
                                    <th>Optionals</th>
                                    <th>Minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>5</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td>English, Mathematics, Science, Social Science</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <h3>Classes 9-12 (Stream-based Structure)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Class:</b> Enter the class number (e.g. 9, 10, 11,..etc)</li>
                            <li><b>Semester:</b> Leave empty</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> Subjects that are common across all streams</li>
                            <li><b>Optionals:</b>Subjects that vary by stream</li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Minors:</b> Usually not applicable in most schools; leave empty unless your school
                                follows a different structure.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Class</th>
                                    <th>Semester</th>
                                    <th>Majors (Common Subjects)</th>
                                    <th>Optionals (Stream Subjects)</th>
                                    <th>Minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>11</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td>English Language, English Literature</td>
                                    <td>Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, Biology, Accounts, Economics, History,
                                        Geography, Hindi</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <p>
                            <b class="error">
                                NOTE: Once again, for classes 9-12, major column only contains those subjects that are
                                common to all streams.
                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b class="tip">
                                For example, if <em>English Language</em> and <em>English Literature</em> are the only
                                subjects common across all streams in your school, then enter only these subjects in the
                                <b>Majors</b> column. All other stream-specific subjects should be entered under the
                                <b>Optionals</b> column.
                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <b class="error">
                                NOTE: Also for any class, If PT or Games periods are conducted and attendance is required, include
                                them in the <b>Majors</b> column. System won't mark attendance for such periods, if it
                                isn't mentioned in your excel sheet.
                            </b>
                        </p>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Class</th>
                                    <th>Semester</th>
                                    <th>Majors</th>
                                    <th>Optionals</th>
                                    <th>Minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>10</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td>English Language, English Literature, Physical Training, Games</td>
                                    <td>Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, Biology, History, Geography, Accounts, Commerce
                                    </td>
                                    <td></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                        <h2>“Common Mistakes” callout</h2>
                        <ul class="font-styling">
                            <li>
                                Do not enter stream-specific subjects (Physics, Accounts, History, etc.) in the
                                <b>Majors</b> column for Classes 9–12.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Do not leave the <b>Majors</b> column empty. At least one common subject must be
                                provided.
                            </li>
                            <li>Do not create separate rows for different streams of the same class.</li>
                            <li>
                                If PT or Games attendance is required, do not forget to include them in the
                                <b>Majors</b> column.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>College Use Case~</h2>
                        <p>College structures are usually semester-based and more straightforward.</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <b>Class:</b> Enter the department name in short form. (e.g. CSE, EEE, EE, ME...etc)
                            </li>
                            <li><b>Semester:</b> Enter semester number (e.g. 1, 2, 3, 4..etc)</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> Core Subjects</li>
                            <li><b>Optionals:</b> Electives, if any.</li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Minors:</b> If Applicable.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><b>Example:</b></p>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Class</th>
                                    <th>Semester</th>
                                    <th>Majors</th>
                                    <th>Optionals</th>
                                    <th>Minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>CSE</td>
                                    <td>5</td>
                                    <td>DBMS, Operating Systems, Computer Networks</td>
                                    <td>AI, Machine Learning</td>
                                    <td>Cyber Security</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
